message: Removed Unsourced claims. Please cite proper sources rather than baseless claims before editing.
Removed some misinformation and some Unsourced claims.
Removed misleading information so that the article reflects a neutral point of view.

Added and also corrected few points. \nShakta texts such as Mahabhagwat Purana, Devi Purana, Shiva Purana and other tantrik texts depict all the Mahavidyas to be the form of Parvati. Hence, Kamala Mahavidya is also related to Parvati. \nFurther, Todala Tantra mentions Kamala to be the wife of Sadashiva which ultimately clarifies that Kamala is a manifestation of Devi Parvati.

Removed Unsourced Claims. Also, Kamala and Lakshmi are different , although they both have a similar name i.e, "Kamala" but they are two distinct goddesses. Unlike Lakshmi, Kamala is a Tantrik Goddess.
Matangi and Saraswati are different according to Tantrik Texts, although they both have a similar iconography.
Removed unsourced claims. Please provide reliable sources before editing.
Removed Unsourced Claims by Random IP.
Added 2 links according to some facts.
